menu "breadboard: bb_sse_writer"

config BB_SSE_SEND_TIMEOUT_MS
    int "SSE-write send timeout (ms)"
    default 3000
    range 500 30000
    help
        SSE-write send timeout in ms; a stalled client send is abandoned after
        this interval so the socket and async httpd session are reclaimed.

config BB_SSE_RECV_TIMEOUT_MS
    int "SSE-write receive timeout (ms)"
    default 30000
    range 1000 120000
    help
        SSE-write receive timeout in ms (SO_RCVTIMEO); surfaces dead peers on
        the read path. Default 30000 (= 2x the 15 s heartbeat interval).

config BB_SSE_ABORT_POLL_MS
    int "SSE peer-abort poll interval (ms)"
    default 1000
    range 100 15000
    help
        Maximum slice of the wait_fn/heartbeat interval between peer-abort
        (MSG_PEEK) checks. The outer SSE loop only re-checks for a dead peer
        when wait_fn returns, which can otherwise take up to heartbeat_ms
        (e.g. 15 s) on a quiet topic — during that window an aborted
        connection's socket lingers, retaining lwIP PCB/pbuf resources
        (B1-517). Lowering this value detects abort sooner at the cost of
        more frequent (non-blocking) peek syscalls; it does not change the
        heartbeat cadence itself.

endmenu
